<HEADLINE>
FT  10 MAR 93 / Leaders press case for aid
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
GREATER urgency in providing Russia with western aid was urged by President
Francois Mitterrand of France and US president Bill Clinton after talks in
Washington yesterday. Mr Clinton favoured early action even though Japan has
signalled opposition to holding an emergency meeting of the Group of Seven
leading industrial nations before its normal summit which is due in Tokyo in
July. The leader wanted the west to move 'aggressively' to help Russia.
