<DATELINE>
   BASLE
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
MR Jacques de Larosiere, governor of the Bank of France, said yesterday the
outlook for inflation in the global economy was positive, Reuter reports
from Basle.
'There is no expectation of a rekindling of inflation, so that bodes well
for the world economy,' he told reporters at the Bank for International
Settlements (BIS).
He added that interest rates for long-term financial instruments had fallen
dramatically over the last month.
'If you look at US interest rates for 10-year instruments, you've got a 60
basis points fall,' he said after the regular monthly meeting of Group of
Ten central bank governors.
