<TEXT>
SAO PAULO advanced 8.1 per cent in heavy trading, the Bovespa index
finishing 1,124 up at 14,974.
Trading was nervous after press reports on Sunday that Mr Paulo Haddad, the
former Brazilian economy minister, had planned a price freeze as a way to
stabilise the economy. Mr Eliseu Resende, Mr Haddad's successor, has said
that he might use elements of Mr Haddad's anti-inflation plan.
