FT  09 MAR 93 / International Company News: Earnings at Federated reach
Dollars 113m for year
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
FEDERATED Department Stores, which emerged from bankruptcy last year and
includes large department store chains such as Bloomingdale's, The Bon
Marche and Jordan Marsh, yesterday reported after-tax profits of Dollars
113m for the 12 months to January 30.
The figure was reached on sales up to Dollars 7.08bn from Dollars 6.93bn,
and compared with a net profits figure of Dollars 836.4m in the previous
year.
However, the 1991-92 result was struck after various one-time items,
including a Dollars 2.1bn extraordinary gain and a Dollars 1.68bn
reorganisation charge.
In the final quarter of 1992-93, Federated made an after-tax profit of
Dollars 99m, on sales up from Dollars 2.13bn to Dollars 2.26bn. Mr Allen
Questrom, Federated's chairman, said the group was very pleased with the
year's performance.
