<HEADLINE>
FT  09 MAR 93 / UK Company News: Greggs improves to Pounds 6.97m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
GREGGS, the bread, confect-ionery and savoury products group, reported a 15
per cent rise, from Pounds 6.07m to Pounds 6.97m, in pre-tax profits for the
year to December 26. The result, taking in a Pounds 134,000 loss on a
property disposal, was achieved on turnover up 6 per cent to Pounds 101m,
against Pounds 95.5m.
Describing 1992 as a 'much better year', Mr Mike Darrington, managing
director, said stable ingredient prices, improved efficiency and cost
control had more than offset the effects of recession, increased competition
and further escalation in rents.
The company was trading from 487 outlets at the year end, a net increase of
13. Net cash stood at Pounds 6.7m, up Pounds 1.7m.
Earnings per share rose to 40.6p (36.8p). The proposed final dividend is
10p, making a total of 15p (14.125p).
