<HEADLINE>
FT  09 MAR 93 / UK Company News: M&amp;G Group seeks clients in the US
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NORMA COHEN, Investments Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
M&amp;G Group, Britain's largest unit trust company, has reached agreement with
Dreyfus Corporation, one of the US's largest mutual fund managers, to offer
international equity and fixed interest products to American clients.
The move is M&amp;G's first significant effort to seek clients abroad and
Dreyfus's first foray into international products for its mutual fund and
institutional clients.
Competition for UK domestic unit trust clients generally has intensified
with increasing numbers of firms offering the product while the number of
unitholder accounts is still lower than it was at the end of the industry's
peak year of 1987.
'We realised we were particularly sensitive to UK economic conditions,' said
Mr David Morgan, managing director of M&amp;G Investment Management. M&amp;G's core
mutual fund activities, like those of the rest of the industry, suffered
during the recession as investors shunned the product generally in favor of
safer building society deposits. M&amp;G began searching for a US partner more
than 18 months ago in an effort to diversify its client base overseas.
Mr Morgan said the company was hoping to capitalise on the growing interest
of US pension funds for international fund management services.
Dreyfus Corporation administers more than Pounds 56bn in more than 125
mutual funds around the country, much of it in fixed income products. It is
roughly the fourth largest US mutual fund manager.
M&amp;G will offer two international mutual funds for Dreyfus's clients, one for
retail clients and one aimed at 401K personal pension accounts and
co-mingled pension funds.
</TEXT>
