<HEADLINE>
FT  08 MAR 93 / Union votes to keep political fund
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE 22,000-strong Society of Telecom Executives voted by a majority of 73
per cent to retain its political fund with about 50 per cent of the members
voting in a postal ballot. It was the first union to hold such a ballot
under the government's 10-year rule.
Unlike most unions with political funds, the STE is not affiliated to the
Labour party but union leaders argued it was important to have a fund to
intervene effectively in political debate.
